tafsir[13]{c,v,t}:
  91,1,"Allah takes an oath on the sun and its rising after breaking onto the eastern horizon."
  91,2,"He also takes an oath on the moon when it follows the sun after it has set."
  91,3,"Allah also takes an oath on the day when it reveals whatever is on the face of the earth through its light."
  91,6,"He also takes an oath on the earth: the way it has been spread so that people can live on it."
  91,12,"When the most wretched among them stood up after his people has appointed him for the task."
  91,13,"The Messenger of Allah Saleh (peace be upon him) said to them: “Leave the camel of Allah alone; let it drink on its day and do not pursue it intending evil.”"
  92,1,"Allah takes an oath on the night when it covers whatever is between the heavens and the earth with its darkness."
  92,2,"And Allah takes an oath on the day when it becomes clear and visible."
  92,3,"And He takes an oath on His creating the two genders: The male and female."
  92,6,"And he believes in the substitute Allah has promised him."
  92,7,"I shall soon make performing good deeds and spending in My path easy for him."
  92,9,"Whilst rejecting the substitute and reward Allah has promised him if he spends his wealth in His path."
  92,11,"His wealth that he is miserly with will not benefit him at all when he dies and enters the hellfire."